<section id="h3_000024" data-index="2822">
<h3 data-index="2823"><span class="red" data-index="2824">Balance Sheet</span></h3>
<p data-index="2825">The balance sheet for Uptown, shown in <a class="blue" id="c03-fig-0043-1" href="#c03-fig-0043" data-index="2826" data-section-index="13" data-section-idref="c03-fig-0043" data-target-data-index="2828"><b data-index="2827">Illustration 3.43</b></a>, is a classified balance sheet. Interest receivable, inventory, prepaid insurance, and prepaid rent are included as current assets. Uptown considers these assets current because they will be converted into cash or used by the business within a relatively short period of time. Uptown deducts the amount of Allowance for Doubtful Accounts from the total of accounts, notes, and interest receivable because it estimates that only $54,800 of $57,800 will be collected in cash.</p>
