<p data-index="7811">Adjustment data:</p>
<p class="latin1" data-index="7812"><span class="label" data-index="7813"><b data-index="7814">1.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> Supplies on hand totaled $1,500.</p>
<p class="latin1" data-index="7815"><span class="label" data-index="7816"><b data-index="7817">2.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> Depreciation is $15,000 on the equipment.</p>
<p class="latin1" data-index="7818"><span class="label" data-index="7819"><b data-index="7820">3.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> Interest of $11,000 is accrued on notes payable at November 30.</p>
<p data-index="7821">Other data:</p>
<p class="latin1" data-index="7822"><span class="label" data-index="7823"><b data-index="7824">1.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> Salaries expense is 70% selling and 30% administrative.</p>
<p class="latin1" data-index="7825"><span class="label" data-index="7826"><b data-index="7827">2.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> Rent expense and utilities expenses are 80% selling and 20% administrative.</p>
<p class="latin1" data-index="7828"><span class="label" data-index="7829"><b data-index="7830">3.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> $30,000 of notes payable are due for payment next year.</p>
<p class="latin1" data-index="7831"><span class="label" data-index="7832"><b data-index="7833">4.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> Maintenance and repairs expense is 100% administrative.</p>
<h4 data-index="7834"><span class="red" data-index="7835">Instructions</span></h4>
<p class="latin1" data-index="7836"><span class="label" data-index="7837"><b data-index="7838">a.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> Journalize the adjusting entries.</p>
<p class="latin1" data-index="7839"><span class="label" data-index="7840"><b data-index="7841">b.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> Prepare an adjusted trial balance.</p>
<p class="latin1" data-index="7842"><span class="label" data-index="7843"><b data-index="7844">c.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> Prepare a multiple-step income statement (ignore taxes) and retained earnings statement for the year and a classified balance sheet as of November 30, 2020.</p>
